{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I'm going to talk about compassion and the golden rule"},{"time":5000,"text":"from a secular perspective and even from a kind of scientific perspective."},{"time":11000,"text":"I'm going to try to give you a little bit of a natural history"},{"time":14000,"text":"of compassion and the golden rule."},{"time":16000,"text":"So, I'm going to be sometimes using kind of clinical language,"},{"time":21000,"text":"and so it's not going to sound as warm and fuzzy"},{"time":23000,"text":"as your average compassion talk."},{"time":25000,"text":"I want to warn you about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"So, I do want to say, at the outset, that I think compassion's great."},{"time":32000,"text":"The golden rule is great. I'm a big supporter of both."},{"time":35000,"text":"And I think it's great that"},{"time":37000,"text":"the leaders of the religions of the world"},{"time":40000,"text":"are affirming compassion and the golden rule as fundamental principles"},{"time":45000,"text":"that are integral to their faiths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48000,"text":"At the same time, I think religions don't deserve all the credit."},{"time":51000,"text":"I think nature gave them a helping hand here."},{"time":55000,"text":"I'm going to argue tonight that compassion and the golden rule"},{"time":60000,"text":"are, in a certain sense, built into human nature."},{"time":63000,"text":"But I'm also going to argue"},{"time":65000,"text":"that once you understand the sense in which they are built into human nature,"},{"time":69000,"text":"you realize that just affirming compassion,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and affirming the golden rule, is really not enough."},{"time":76000,"text":"There's a lot of work to be done after that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"OK so, a quick natural history, first of compassion."},{"time":84000,"text":"In the beginning, there was compassion,"},{"time":87000,"text":"and I mean not just when human beings first showed up,"},{"time":90000,"text":"but actually even before that."},{"time":92000,"text":"I think it's probably the case that, in the human evolutionary lineage,"},{"time":96000,"text":"even before there were homo sapiens,"},{"time":99000,"text":"feelings like compassion and love and sympathy"},{"time":101000,"text":"had earned their way into the gene pool,"},{"time":105000,"text":"and biologists have a pretty clear idea of how this first happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"It happened through a principle known as kin selection."},{"time":112000,"text":"And the basic idea of kin selection is that,"},{"time":118000,"text":"if an animal feels compassion for a close relative,"},{"time":121000,"text":"and this compassion leads the animal to help the relative,"},{"time":125000,"text":"then, in the end, the compassion actually winds up helping the genes"},{"time":130000,"text":"underlying the compassion itself."},{"time":133000,"text":"So, from a biologist's point of view, compassion is actually"},{"time":137000,"text":"a gene's way of helping itself. OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"I warned you this was not going to be very warm and fuzzy."},{"time":145000,"text":"I'll get there -- I hope to get a little fuzzier."},{"time":148000,"text":"This doesn't bother me so much,"},{"time":150000,"text":"that the underlying Darwinian rationale of compassion"},{"time":154000,"text":"is kind of self-serving at the genetic level."},{"time":156000,"text":"Actually, I think the bad news about kin selection"},{"time":159000,"text":"is just that it means that this kind of compassion"},{"time":163000,"text":"is naturally deployed only within the family."},{"time":166000,"text":"That's the bad news. The good news is compassion is natural."},{"time":169000,"text":"The bad news is that this kin selected compassion"},{"time":172000,"text":"is naturally confined to the family."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"Now, there's more good news that came along later in evolution,"},{"time":178000,"text":"a second kind of evolutionary logic."},{"time":181000,"text":"Biologists call that \"reciprocal altruism.\" OK."},{"time":184000,"text":"And there, the basic idea is that"},{"time":187000,"text":"compassion leads you to do good things for people who then will return the favor."},{"time":195000,"text":"Again, I know this is not as inspiring a notion of compassion"},{"time":200000,"text":"as you may have heard in the past,"},{"time":202000,"text":"but from a biologist's point of view, this reciprocal altruism kind of compassion"},{"time":207000,"text":"is ultimately self-serving too."},{"time":210000,"text":"It's not that people think that, when they feel the compassion."},{"time":212000,"text":"It's not consciously self-serving, but to a biologist, that's the logic."},{"time":217000,"text":"And so, you wind up most easily extending compassion to friends and allies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223000,"text":"I'm sure a lot of you, if a close friend has something really terrible happen to them,"},{"time":229000,"text":"you feel really bad."},{"time":231000,"text":"But if you read in the newspaper"},{"time":232000,"text":"that something really horrible happened to somebody you've never heard of,"},{"time":235000,"text":"you can probably live with that."},{"time":237000,"text":"That's just human nature."},{"time":239000,"text":"So, it's another good news/bad news story."},{"time":241000,"text":"It's good that compassion was extended beyond the family"},{"time":243000,"text":"by this kind of evolutionary logic."},{"time":245000,"text":"The bad news is this doesn't bring us universal compassion by itself."},{"time":250000,"text":"So, there's still work to be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"Now, there's one other result of this dynamic called reciprocal altruism,"},{"time":257000,"text":"which I think is kind of good news,"},{"time":259000,"text":"which is that the way that this is played out in the human species,"},{"time":263000,"text":"it has given people an intuitive appreciation of the golden rule."},{"time":267000,"text":"I don't quite mean that the golden rule itself is written in our genes,"},{"time":271000,"text":"but you can go to a hunter gatherer society"},{"time":275000,"text":"that has had no exposure to any of the great religious traditions,"},{"time":278000,"text":"no exposure to ethical philosophy,"},{"time":280000,"text":"and you'll find, if you spend time with these people,"},{"time":282000,"text":"that, basically, they believe that one good turn deserves another,"},{"time":285000,"text":"and that bad deeds should be punished."},{"time":287000,"text":"And evolutionary psychologists think that these intuitions have a basis in the genes."},{"time":293000,"text":"So, they do understand that if you want to be treated well,"},{"time":297000,"text":"you treat other people well."},{"time":299000,"text":"And it's good to treat other people well."},{"time":301000,"text":"That's close to being a kind of built-in intuition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"So, that's good news. Now, if you've been paying attention,"},{"time":308000,"text":"you're probably anticipating that there's bad news here;"},{"time":311000,"text":"we still aren't to universal love,"},{"time":313000,"text":"and it's true because, although an appreciation of the golden rule is natural,"},{"time":318000,"text":"it's also natural to carve out exceptions to the golden rule."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"I mean, for example, none of us, probably, want to go to prison,"},{"time":327000,"text":"but we all think that there are some people who should go to prison. Right?"},{"time":330000,"text":"So, we think we should treat them differently than we would want to be treated."},{"time":334000,"text":"Now, we have a rationale for that."},{"time":336000,"text":"We say they did these bad things that make it just that they should go to prison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"None of us really extends the golden rule in truly diffuse and universal fashion."},{"time":345000,"text":"We have the capacity to carve out exceptions,"},{"time":348000,"text":"put people in a special category."},{"time":350000,"text":"And the problem is that -- although in the case of sending people to prison,"},{"time":354000,"text":"you have this impartial judiciary"},{"time":357000,"text":"determining who gets excluded from the golden rule --"},{"time":361000,"text":"that in everyday life, the way we all make these decisions"},{"time":365000,"text":"about who we're not going to extend the golden rule to,"},{"time":368000,"text":"is we use a much rougher and readier formula."},{"time":371000,"text":"Basically it's just like, if you're my enemy, if you're my rival --"},{"time":375000,"text":"if you're not my friend, if you're not in my family --"},{"time":377000,"text":"I'm much less inclined to apply the golden rule to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"We all do that,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and you see it all over the world."},{"time":387000,"text":"You see it in the Middle East:"},{"time":390000,"text":"people who, from Gaza, are firing missiles at Israel."},{"time":393000,"text":"They wouldn't want to have missiles fired at them, but they say,"},{"time":395000,"text":"\"Well, but the Israelis, or some of them have done things"},{"time":397000,"text":"that put them in a special category.\""},{"time":399000,"text":"The Israelis would not want to have an economic blockade imposed on them,"},{"time":402000,"text":"but they impose one on Gaza, and they say,"},{"time":404000,"text":"\"Well, the Palestinians, or some of them, have brought this on themselves.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"So, it's these exclusions to the golden rule that amount to a lot of the world's trouble."},{"time":415000,"text":"And it's natural to do that."},{"time":418000,"text":"So, the fact that the golden rule is in some sense built in to us"},{"time":421000,"text":"is not, by itself, going to bring us universal love."},{"time":427000,"text":"It's not going to save the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"Now, there's one piece of good news I have that may save the world. Okay."},{"time":434000,"text":"Are you on the edges of your seats here?"},{"time":437000,"text":"Good, because before I tell you about that good news,"},{"time":439000,"text":"I'm going to have to take a little excursion through some academic terrain."},{"time":444000,"text":"So, I hope I've got your attention with this promise of good news"},{"time":447000,"text":"that may save the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450000,"text":"It's this non-zero-sumness stuff you just heard a little bit about."},{"time":453000,"text":"It's just a quick introduction to game theory."},{"time":456000,"text":"This won't hurt. Okay."},{"time":458000,"text":"It's about zero-sum and non-zero-sum games."},{"time":460000,"text":"If you ask what kind of a situation"},{"time":464000,"text":"is conducive to people becoming friends and allies,"},{"time":467000,"text":"the technical answer is a non-zero-sum situation."},{"time":470000,"text":"And if you ask what kind of situation"},{"time":472000,"text":"is conducive to people defining people as enemies,"},{"time":474000,"text":"it's a zero-sum situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"So, what do those terms mean?"},{"time":478000,"text":"Basically, a zero-sum game is the kind you're used to in sports,"},{"time":481000,"text":"where there's a winner and a loser."},{"time":483000,"text":"So, their fortunes add up to zero."},{"time":486000,"text":"So, in tennis, every point is either good for you and bad for the other person,"},{"time":491000,"text":"or good for them, bad for you."},{"time":493000,"text":"Either way, your fortunes add up to zero. That's a zero-sum game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"Now, if you're playing doubles,"},{"time":498000,"text":"then the person on your side of the net"},{"time":500000,"text":"is in a non-zero-sum relationship with you,"},{"time":503000,"text":"because every point is either good for both of you -- positive, win-win --"},{"time":506000,"text":"or bad for both of you, it's lose-lose."},{"time":508000,"text":"That's a non-zero-sum game."},{"time":510000,"text":"And in real life, there are lots of non-zero-sum games."},{"time":513000,"text":"In the realm of economics, say, if you buy something:"},{"time":516000,"text":"that means you'd rather have the merchandise than the money,"},{"time":519000,"text":"but the merchant would rather have the money than the merchandise."},{"time":522000,"text":"You both feel you've won."},{"time":524000,"text":"In a war, two allies are playing a non-zero-sum game."},{"time":527000,"text":"It's going to either be win-win or lose-lose for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"So, there are lots of non-zero-sum games in real life."},{"time":537000,"text":"And you could basically reformulate what I said earlier,"},{"time":541000,"text":"about how compassion is deployed and the golden rule is deployed,"},{"time":544000,"text":"by just saying, well, compassion most naturally flows along non-zero-sum channels"},{"time":550000,"text":"where people perceive themselves as being in a potentially win-win situation"},{"time":553000,"text":"with some of their friends or allies."},{"time":556000,"text":"The deployment of the golden rule"},{"time":558000,"text":"most naturally happens along these non-zero-sum channels."},{"time":561000,"text":"So, kind of webs of non-zero-sumness"},{"time":563000,"text":"are where you would expect compassion and the golden rule"},{"time":567000,"text":"to kind of work their magic."},{"time":569000,"text":"With zero-sum channels you would expect something else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"Okay. So, now you're ready for the good news that I said might save the world."},{"time":575000,"text":"And now I can admit that it might not too,"},{"time":578000,"text":"now that I've held your attention for three minutes of technical stuff."},{"time":584000,"text":"But it may. And the good news is that history"},{"time":589000,"text":"has naturally expanded these webs of non-zero-sumness,"},{"time":593000,"text":"these webs that can be these channels for compassion."},{"time":597000,"text":"You can go back all the way to the stone age:"},{"time":600000,"text":"technological evolution -- roads, the wheel, writing,"},{"time":608000,"text":"a lot of transportation and communication technologies --"},{"time":611000,"text":"has just inexorably made it so that more people"},{"time":614000,"text":"can be in more non-zero-sum relationships"},{"time":617000,"text":"with more and more people at greater and greater distances."},{"time":620000,"text":"That's the story of civilization."},{"time":623000,"text":"It's why social organization has grown from the hunter-gatherer village"},{"time":628000,"text":"to the ancient state, the empire, and now here we are in a globalized world."},{"time":631000,"text":"And the story of globalization is largely a story of non-zero-sumness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"You've probably heard the term \"interdependence\""},{"time":637000,"text":"applied to the modern world. Well, that's just another term for non-zero-sum."},{"time":641000,"text":"If your fortunes are interdependent with somebody,"},{"time":644000,"text":"then you live in a non-zero-sum relationship with them."},{"time":647000,"text":"And you see this all the time in the modern world."},{"time":649000,"text":"You saw it with the recent economic crash,"},{"time":651000,"text":"where bad things happen in the economy --"},{"time":654000,"text":"bad for everybody, for much of the world."},{"time":657000,"text":"Good things happen, and it's good for much of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660000,"text":"And, you know, I'm happy to say, I think there's really evidence"},{"time":663000,"text":"that this non-zero-sum kind of connection"},{"time":666000,"text":"can expand the moral compass."},{"time":669000,"text":"I mean, if you look at the American attitudes"},{"time":672000,"text":"toward Japanese during World War II --"},{"time":676000,"text":"look at the depictions of Japanese"},{"time":678000,"text":"in the American media as just about subhuman,"},{"time":680000,"text":"and look at the fact that we dropped atomic bombs,"},{"time":682000,"text":"really without giving it much of a thought --"},{"time":685000,"text":"and you compare that to the attitude now,"},{"time":687000,"text":"I think part of that is due to a kind of economic interdependence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690000,"text":"Any form of interdependence, or non-zero-sum relationship"},{"time":693000,"text":"forces you to acknowledge the humanity of people."},{"time":696000,"text":"So, I think that's good."},{"time":698000,"text":"And the world is full of non-zero-sum dynamics."},{"time":701000,"text":"Environmental problems, in many ways, put us all in the same boat."},{"time":705000,"text":"And there are non-zero-sum relationships that maybe people aren't aware of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710000,"text":"For example, probably a lot of American Christians"},{"time":714000,"text":"don't think of themselves as being in a non-zero-sum relationship"},{"time":718000,"text":"with Muslims halfway around the world,"},{"time":720000,"text":"but they really are, because if these Muslims become happier and happier"},{"time":725000,"text":"with their place in the world and feel that they have a place in it,"},{"time":728000,"text":"that's good for Americans, because there will be fewer terrorists"},{"time":731000,"text":"to threaten American security."},{"time":733000,"text":"If they get less and less happy, that will be bad for Americans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"So, there's plenty of non-zero-sumness."},{"time":740000,"text":"And so, the question is: If there's so much non-zero-sumness,"},{"time":745000,"text":"why has the world not yet been suffused in love, peace, and understanding?"},{"time":749000,"text":"The answer's complicated. It's the occasion for a whole other talk."},{"time":752000,"text":"Certainly, a couple of things are that,"},{"time":756000,"text":"first of all, there are a lot of zero-sum situations in the world."},{"time":760000,"text":"And also, sometimes people don't recognize"},{"time":764000,"text":"the non-zero-sum dynamics in the world."},{"time":769000,"text":"In both of these areas,"},{"time":771000,"text":"I think politicians can play a role."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774000,"text":"This isn't only about religion."},{"time":776000,"text":"I think politicians can help foster non-zero-sum relationships,"},{"time":781000,"text":"Economic engagement is generally better than blockades and so on,"},{"time":784000,"text":"in this regard."},{"time":786000,"text":"And politicians can be aware, and should be aware that,"},{"time":789000,"text":"when people around the world are looking at them,"},{"time":791000,"text":"are looking at their nation"},{"time":793000,"text":"and picking up their cues"},{"time":795000,"text":"for whether they are in a zero-sum or a non-zero-sum relationship with a nation --"},{"time":799000,"text":"like, say, America, or any other nation --"},{"time":802000,"text":"human psychology is such that they use cues like:"},{"time":805000,"text":"Do we feel we're being respected?"},{"time":807000,"text":"Because, you know, historically, if you're not being respected,"},{"time":810000,"text":"you're probably not going to wind up in a non-zero-sum,"},{"time":813000,"text":"mutually profitable relationship with people."},{"time":816000,"text":"So, we need to be aware of what kind of signals we're sending out."},{"time":821000,"text":"And some of this, again, is in the realm of political work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826000,"text":"If there's one thing I can encourage everyone to do,"},{"time":828000,"text":"politicians, religious leaders, and us,"},{"time":831000,"text":"it would be what I call \"expanding the moral imagination\" --"},{"time":836000,"text":"that is to say, your ability to put yourself in the shoes"},{"time":839000,"text":"of people in very different circumstances."},{"time":842000,"text":"This is not the same as compassion,"},{"time":844000,"text":"but it's conducive to compassion. It opens the channels for compassion."},{"time":850000,"text":"And I'm afraid we have another good news/bad news story,"},{"time":853000,"text":"which is that the moral imagination is part of human nature."},{"time":856000,"text":"That's good, but again we tend to deploy it selectively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861000,"text":"Once we define somebody as an enemy,"},{"time":863000,"text":"we have trouble putting ourselves in their shoes, just naturally."},{"time":868000,"text":"So, if you want to take a particularly hard case for an American:"},{"time":872000,"text":"somebody in Iran who is burning an American flag, and you see them on TV."},{"time":876000,"text":"Well, the average American is going to resist"},{"time":879000,"text":"the moral exercise of putting themselves in that person's head"},{"time":883000,"text":"and is going to resist the idea that they have much in common with that person."},{"time":886000,"text":"And if you tell them, \"Well, they think America disrespects them"},{"time":890000,"text":"and even wants to dominate them, and they hate America."},{"time":893000,"text":"Has there ever been somebody who disrespected you so much"},{"time":895000,"text":"that you kind of hated them briefly\"?"},{"time":897000,"text":"You know, they'll resist that comparison and that's natural, that's human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900000,"text":"And, similarly, the person in Iran:"},{"time":902000,"text":"when you try to humanize somebody in America who said that Islam is evil,"},{"time":906000,"text":"they'll have trouble with that."},{"time":908000,"text":"So, it's a very difficult thing to get people to expand the moral imagination"},{"time":913000,"text":"to a place it doesn't naturally go."},{"time":916000,"text":"I think it's worth the trouble because,"},{"time":919000,"text":"again, it just helps us to understand."},{"time":921000,"text":"If you want to reduce the number of people who are burning flags,"},{"time":923000,"text":"it helps to understand what makes them do it."},{"time":925000,"text":"And I think it's good moral exercise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"I would say here is where religious leaders come in,"},{"time":931000,"text":"because religious leaders are good at reframing issues for people,"},{"time":938000,"text":"at harnessing the emotional centers of the brain"},{"time":940000,"text":"to get people to alter their awareness and reframe the way they think."},{"time":945000,"text":"I mean, religious leaders are kind of in the inspiration business."},{"time":949000,"text":"It's their great calling right now,"},{"time":951000,"text":"to get people all around the world better at expanding their moral imaginations,"},{"time":955000,"text":"appreciating that in so many ways they're in the same boat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959000,"text":"I would just sum up the way things look, at least from this secular perspective,"},{"time":965000,"text":"as far as compassion and the golden rule go,"},{"time":969000,"text":"by saying that it's good news that compassion and the golden rule"},{"time":975000,"text":"are in some sense built into human nature."},{"time":980000,"text":"It's unfortunate that they tend to be selectively deployed."},{"time":985000,"text":"And it's going to take real work to change that."},{"time":989000,"text":"But, nobody ever said that doing God's work was going to be easy. Thanks."},{"time":994000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}